reviews.review_text: Boston Run Definate upgrade from the the other source found here. The Boston run from 91 were some the best shows i saw them perform.

Another 5 star rating after Brent!!! This show absolutely smokes.  One of my favorite first sets of the 90's.  Bruce is ALL over the BIODTL, Big RxR, and the All Over Now.  Hot Stranger and Althea also.  Such a great SBD.  Boston 91 the band is on fire!!  They never let up during all 6 shows.  The second is sizzlin' as well.  Great China > Rider and Dark Star pre drums and I love the Foolish out of space, unusual slot.  I could listen to Fall 91 shows all day!!!
better have a super volume booster on your stereo

sick! still makes my hair stand after almost 15 years!
I MISS THE BOYS! AND THE GARDEN!
yo yo grateful dead!  very clean mix!

one of my favs.... this show will always be a special one for me.  I was 2nd row in front of Phil w/my GD touring buddy..and it was magic from the get go.

very strong 1st set.
awesome 2nd set with amazing energy.  odd little Dark Star..but nice.  
SOTM was HUGE.  Jerry almost melted my head with those last crazy midi-fied solos.  He was looking over the rim of his glasses right at me while he sang it.  well, in my general direction any way.
you know that Jerry "over the glasses" look.
:-)

I think this show is very under rated, and prefer it over any other night of the run.  9-22 and 9-26 tied for 2nd.

4- overall I do think that SOTM is the highlight of the show. The Foolish out of space is very neat for nostalgic purposes, but it isn't all that great overall. The rest of the show has it's moments, but I think overall this show is barely a 4.

Not Great, Not Inspired, Not Anything but Pretty Good Good recording and remaster. Fairly decent performance. A nice plate of spaghetti. Luscious background and ambience music for a dinner party. Not great vintage but highly drinkable.
Desolation Row Great version of one of my favorite GD tunes.
